Dynamic sidebox display template for SemanticSchemas categories.

Composes display-header, the property rows, render-reverse, and
subobjects into a floating sidebar layout. See `Category/table` for the
fast-path / dynamic-fallback parameter contract — this template is
identical apart from the outer chrome.

Parameters:
* category - The category name (without namespace prefix). Required.
* label    - Optional baked category display label.
* props    - Optional comma-separated parameter-name list that triggers
             the baked row path.
* val_<p>  - Per-property value, one per entry in `props`.
* label_<p> - Per-property display label, one per entry in `props`.
* page     - Target page on the dynamic row path. Defaults to
             {{FULLPAGENAME}}.
* subobjects - Set to "no" to suppress the subobject and backlink
             sections.
</noinclude>
